Are all gradients the same?

No.

This is where I’d start making distinctions.

There are energy gradients.
Information gradients.
Value gradients.
Uncertainty gradients.
Competence gradients.
Social gradients.
Reward gradients.

Mathematically, many can be described as “a direction of change,” but mechanistically they’re different.

Yet…

there’s an interesting commonality.

A gradient says:

“Movement is not equivalent in every direction.”

That’s profound.

Without gradients, every direction is equally good.

Nothing pulls.

Nothing pushes.

Nothing matters.

Gradients create asymmetry.

Asymmetry creates direction.

Direction makes search possible.

